 :tx/rationale "C9-STEERING-QUESTION-INSIGHT: After internalizing STEERING_MANIFOLD.md, the critical missing element in C9-P5 is THE QUESTION. Section 2 of STEERING_MANIFOLD.md shows the gold standard: every braid observe response ends with a computed question that targets the boundary between concepts — the highest-surprise region. The current C9-P5 design groups, ranks, and shows graph context. That is structured data. It activates the LLM's 'reading a report' mode. Adding a steering question at the end activates the 'investigating a lead' mode. The difference is the difference between a filing cabinet and a cognitive partner. SPECIFIC ADDITIONS TO C9-P5: (1) braid observe list ends with: '-> What connects [concept-A] and [concept-B]?' where A and B are the top bridge-gap pair from co_occurrence_matrix with zero jaccard. This steers toward the highest-information-gain investigation. (2) braid observe search PATTERN ends with: '-> [first unresolved finding from results]' or '-> N findings corroborated by M agents — consider: [top convergent action]'. Steers toward synthesis of search results. (3) braid observe show ENTITY ends with: '-> [most surprising unlinked neighbor]' computed from concept membership — an entity in the same concept that this observation has no link to. Steers toward graph completion. (4) braid observe recent N ends with: '-> Recent theme: [dominant concept]. Gap: [unexplored concept with fewest recent observations]'. Steers toward coverage balance. THESE QUESTIONS ARE COMPUTED, NOT GENERATED. They use existing functions: frontier_recommendation(), co_occurrence_matrix(), concept_inventory(). Zero LLM calls. The question IS the acquisition function rendered as natural language — alpha(action) = E[delta_F(S)]/cost expressed as a Socratic prompt. TRACES TO: STEERING_MANIFOLD.md Section 2, ADR-FOUNDATION-030 (FEGH), INV-GUIDANCE-001 (continuous injection)."
